Step 1:

Create a pod with init, main containers :

apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: business-app
spec:
  volumes:
    - name: shared-data
      emptyDir: {}

  initContainers:
    - name: configurer
      image: busybox:1.36.1
      command:
        - sh
        - -c
        - wget -O /usr/shared/app/config.json https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bmuschko/ckad-crash-course/master/exercises/07-init-container/app/config/config.json
      volumeMounts:
        - name: shared-data
          mountPath: /usr/shared/app

  containers:
    - name: web
      image: bmuschko/nodejs-read-config:1.0.0
      ports:
        - containerPort: 8080
      volumeMounts:
        - name: shared-data
          mountPath: /usr/shared/app

kubectl logs business-app -c configurer

Step 2 : 

Access the application container

C:\Users\thani\Kubernetes>kubectl exec -it business-app -c web -- sh
# curl localhost:8080
Database URL: localhost:5432/customers
#


Debugging Init Container Issues

	Checking init container logs: kubectl logs business-app -c configurer
	
	Describing the Pod to inspect events and exit codes: kubectl describe pod business-app

